    skos:definition "Natural areas dominated by tree cover that is generally over 6 meters, or 20 feet, in height. The forest cover must occur in an upland setting with an understory of natural plant material or ground cover. If the understory has been altered to accommodate an agricultural or urban land use activity, such as a pasture or park, the area would be assigned to the appropriate land use type. Forest cover occurring in wetland environments would be assigned to the forested wetland group"@en ;
