    skos:broadMatch ex:Forest ;
    skos:definition "Use Min. Area (ha) = 0.1 Min. Crown Cover (%) = 30 Min. Tree Height (m) = Min. Strip Width (m) = ns National Forest Legislation defines forested lands as forested lands of the forest fund occupied by young forest of timber species with stand density of 0.4 and higher, and stands of other age groups with stand density of 0.3 and higher, as well as areas occupied by bushes, at which stands of timber species cannot be developed without special forest improvement.. 0.1 hectare is adopted as a minimal accounting unit of area"@en ;
    skos:inScheme ex:ForestScheme ;
    skos:note "Belarus 2006 KP" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Belarus UNFCCC"@en ;
    skos:scopeNote "National Forest Legislation defines forested lands as forested lands of the forest fund occupied by young forest of timber species with stand density of 0.4 and higher, and stands of other age groups with stand density of 0.3 and higher, as well as areas occupied by bushes, at which stands of timber species cannot be developed without special forest improvement.. 0.1 hectare is adopted as a minimal accounting unit of area. (2006)",
        "National"@en,
        "use"@en .

