    dct:creator "KP" ;
    dct:date "2006"^^xsd:gYear ;
    dct:spatial "Switzerland" ;
    skos:broadMatch ex:Forest ;
    skos:definition "Use Min. Area (ha) = 0.0625-0.25 Min. Crown Cover (%) = 20-60 Min. Tree Height (m) = 3 Min. Strip Width (m) = 25-50 (2006). The following forest areas are not subject to the criterion of minimum stand height: shrub forest consisting of dwarf pine (Pinus mugo prostrata) and alpine alder (Alnus viridis). The following forest areas are not subject of the criteria of minimum stand height and minimum crown cover, but must have the potential to achieve it: afforested, regenerated, as well as burned, cut or damaged areas. Although orchards, parks, camping grounds, open tree formations in settlements, gardens, cemeteries, sports and parking fields may fulfil the (quantitative) forest definition, they are not considered as forests"@en ;
    skos:inScheme ex:ForestScheme ;
    skos:note "Switzerland 2006 KP" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Switzerland UNFCCC"@en ;
    skos:scopeNote "The following forest areas are not subject to the criterion of minimum stand height: shrub forest consisting of dwarf pine (Pinus mugo prostrata) and alpine alder (Alnus viridis). The following forest areas are not subject of the criteria of minimum stand height and minimum crown cover, but must have the potential to achieve it: afforested, regenerated, as well as burned, cut or damaged areas. Although orchards, parks, camping grounds, open tree formations in settlements, gardens, cemeteries, sports and parking fields may fulfil the (quantitative) forest definition, they are not considered as forests.",
        "National"@en,
        "use"@en .

