    skos:definition "Use Min. Area (ha) = 0.5 Min. Crown Cover (%) = 10 Min. Tree Height (m) = 5 Min. Strip Width (m) = 20 , (2006) In addition, the forest area includes temporarily unstocked areas, smaller open areas in the forest needed for management purposes and fire breaks. Forests in national parks, reserves, or areas under special protection are included. Windbreaks and groves covering more than 0.5 ha and with a minimum width of 20 m are also considered as forests. Farmlands, orchards, gardens (houses and summer houses) are NOT included in the forest area"@en ;
